@edewata  -- Ah so I am wrong. :-) JSS does expose a JSSKeyStoreSpi implementation! I love when code appears without me having to write it ;-) And -- we've both also modified this code and forgotten about having done so!
So then, when you wrote the JSSKeyManager / JSSTrustManager implementations originally, they should've taken a KeyStore instance as a parameter and perhaps validated that it was an instance from the Mozilla-JSS provider... When I added the JSSKeyManagerFactory and JSSTrustManagerFactory, they too should've respected the KeyStore parameter... But we haven't done any of that.
Edit: I think it'd be simple enough to add to KeyManager/KeyManagerFactory if we want to. It'd probably even be a good idea. Thoughts?
